1
00:00:02,671 --> 00:00:08,179
This is at the heart
of Kṛṣṇa conception, actually.

2
00:00:08,318 --> 00:00:12,177
[God: Up Close and Personal]

3
00:00:12,940 --> 00:00:18,638
Sometimes Śrila Saraswatī Ṭhākur,
according to Guru Mahārāj

4
00:00:18,638 --> 00:00:22,694
would make some comparisons
between Christianity

5
00:00:22,694 --> 00:00:27,242
as it’s generally understood
in Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

6
00:00:27,242 --> 00:00:33,850
and talk about the Fatherhood of Godhead
and the Sonhood of Godhead.

7
00:00:33,850 --> 00:00:42,252
So there’s this generally 
Judeo–Christian idea of God The Father.

8
00:00:42,252 --> 00:00:45,590
He’s always seen 
in the father position

9
00:00:45,590 --> 00:00:54,843
and as a somewhat remote figure,
maybe even stern.

10
00:00:55,764 --> 00:00:58,729
In the Old Testament,

11
00:00:58,729 --> 00:01:03,004
“Obey Me, lest I smite thee
from the face of the Earth”,

12
00:01:03,004 --> 00:01:12,532
this kind of “You better be obedient or
the wrath of God will be upon you”.

13
00:01:12,532 --> 00:01:20,163
And we know on the Sistine Chapel
in all its glory,

14
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:24,219
still, it’s a stereotypical conception,

15
00:01:24,219 --> 00:01:30,410
anthropomorphic in the sense that God,
we’re being told He’s the oldest,

16
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:33,943
so He must be a very old man
with a big long beard,

17
00:01:33,943 --> 00:01:37,045
because He’s 
the oldest living being.

18
00:01:37,045 --> 00:01:39,454
These kind of things.

19
00:01:39,454 --> 00:01:42,925
And still, 
He’s in the father position.

20
00:01:42,925 --> 00:01:47,664
Then later, they have Jesus.
I’m not gonna go into Christian theology,

21
00:01:47,664 --> 00:01:52,890
but, by contrast, 
in Kṛṣṇa conception,

22
00:01:52,890 --> 00:02:04,228
rather than being a remote figure,
overseer, permitter, bread supplier,

23
00:02:04,228 --> 00:02:08,851
He’s in the centre
of all of these activities.

24
00:02:08,851 --> 00:02:12,981
So, of all the relationships
that we can conceive:

25
00:02:12,981 --> 00:02:20,723
śānta (passive), dāsya (servitorship),
sakhya (friendship),

26
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:26,988
vātsalya (familial love),
to [mādhurya] (conjugal love),

27
00:02:26,988 --> 00:02:35,902
He’s in the centre; He’s at the centre
of all of these possible relationships.

28
00:02:35,917 --> 00:02:40,611
And that centre [is]
akhila rasāmṛta mūrtiḥ,

29
00:02:40,611 --> 00:02:45,780
Rūpa Goswāmī in describing Kṛṣṇa
in the Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu:

30
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:55,750
He’s the nectarine source
of all rasa,

31
00:02:56,265 --> 00:03:00,505
all possible loving exchanges;

32
00:03:00,505 --> 00:03:06,459
the full spectral range of possibility
of any type of loving affectionate exchange,

33
00:03:06,459 --> 00:03:09,366
He can reciprocate that.

34
00:03:09,366 --> 00:03:20,829
The one supreme entity can reciprocate
the hankering of every soul in existence,

35
00:03:20,844 --> 00:03:25,599
everyone in the world.

